To the Editor:
As the committee appointed by Mr.
Wall studies the question of withdraw
ing academic credit from the AFROTC
program, ! suggest that its members
consider whether the issue would be altered if the year were 1944 instead of
1969. For the sake of Grinnell’s charge<
her as a liberal arts college, the answer
should not be “yes."
investing that the academic content of
courses in all departments meet certain minimum standards of quality is a
sound principle by which to modify the
academic curriculum. But educational
concern should not be a present for the
expression of the current opinions of
some members of the college on immediate political issues. When the liberal arts
